Sentencas: The effective conductivity of a thick-film solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrode is an important characteristic used to link the microstructure of the electrode to its performance.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development

Sentencas: A 3D resistor network model that has been developed to determine the effective conductivity of a given SOFC electrode microstructure, the Resistor Network or ResNet model, is introduced in this paper.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development

Sentencas: The model requires the discretization of a 3D microstructure into voxels, based on which a mixed resistor network is drawn.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development

Sentencas: A potential difference is then applied to this network and yields the corresponding currents, allowing the equivalent resistance and hence conductivity of the entire structure to be determined.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development

Sentencas: An overview of the ResNet modeling methodology is presented.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development

Sentencas: The approach is general and can be applied to structures of arbitrary complexity, for which appropriate discretization resolutions are required.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development

Sentencas: The validity of the model is tested by applying it to a set of model structures and comparing calculated effective ;conductivity values against analytical results.
Titulo: Towards the 3D modeling of the effective conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes: I. Model development
